A woman has been killed and three others injured
following a multiple-vehicle collision on the N14 near the Jean Avenue turnoff
in Centurion, on Monday.ER24 paramedics, along with other services, found that a
truck and five light motor vehicles had collided. ER24 spokesman Russel Meiring said all the vehicles were
found lying in the two left lanes of the highway.if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");<a href="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" target="_blank"><img src="https://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=0&sz=1&c=234" border="0" alt=""></a>Multiple-vehicle collision leaves one dead, three injuredParamedics began to assess the situation and found that
one woman had apparently been ejected from her vehicle, now found lying next to
a vehicle on its side. The woman was assessed and found to have sustained
numerous injuries and showed no signs of life. "Unfortunately, nothing could be done for her and
she was declared dead," said Meiring.Three other patients were found on the scene with
injuries ranging from minor to moderate. The patients were treated for their
injuries and were thereafter transported to nearby hospitals by other services.The exact cause of the collision is not yet known but
